# ==============================================================================
# DeCloud Orchestrator — installer environment file (EXAMPLE)
# ==============================================================================
#
# Copy this file, fill in real values, and pass it to the installer:
#
#     sudo install -m 600 /dev/null /etc/decloud/install.env
#     sudo nano /etc/decloud/install.env          # paste + edit (NOT echo >>, see below)
#     sudo bash install.sh --env-file /etc/decloud/install.env \
#          --ingress-domain vms.stackfi.tech \
#          --orchestrator-domain decloud.stackfi.tech \
#          --enable-wireguard
#
# Why: secrets passed as CLI flags land in shell history and `ps` output. This
# file keeps them off the command line. install.sh sources it with `set -a` so
# every variable below is exported into the installer's environment.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RULE 1 — Use the INTERNAL variable names, not the flag names.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The flag is --orchestrator-private-key; the variable is ORCHESTRATOR_PRIVATE_KEY.
# Sourcing this file sets the variables directly, bypassing the flag parser, so
# only the names below work. A typo'd name is silently ignored — the installer
# will fall back to its default or fail a later validation, not tell you the line
# was wrong.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RULE 2 — SECRETS ONLY. Flags with installation side effects MUST stay on the
#          command line.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Some flags do more than set a variable. --ingress-domain also sets
# INSTALL_CADDY=true and ENABLE_INGRESS=true, and INSTALL_CADDY changes how the
# systemd unit is generated (it adds `Requires=caddy.service`, a HARD dependency).
#
# Setting INGRESS_DOMAIN here without the flag produced a working BaseDomain but
# left ENABLE_INGRESS=false, which silently disabled central ingress: new VMs got
# no subdomain, and the only log line was at Debug level. Setting INSTALL_CADDY
# and ENABLE_INGRESS here by hand to compensate made it worse — the orchestrator
# would not start at all.
#
# So: DO NOT put any of these in this file. Pass the flags instead.
#   --ingress-domain    (sets INGRESS_DOMAIN + INSTALL_CADDY + ENABLE_INGRESS)
#   --caddy-staging     (CADDY_STAGING)
#   --enable-wireguard  (ENABLE_WIREGUARD)
#   --no-log            (ENABLE_LOGGING)
#   --force             (FORCE_REBUILD)
#   --skip-fail2ban
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RULE 3 — Quote every value, keep it on ONE line, and mind special characters.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file is sourced by bash. An unquoted or line-wrapped value gets truncated
# or word-split. A MongoDB SRV URI split across lines produced:
#     "LookupDomainName must have at least three components"
# and the orchestrator crashed on startup.
#
# If a password contains $ ` " ' or \, either escape it or (better) URL-encode it
# in the connection string.
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RULE 4 — Never commit the real file; never build it with `echo >>`.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Commit THIS example only. The real file goes at /etc/decloud/install.env with
# mode 600, created via an editor or a quoted heredoc — typing secrets on the
# command line to build the file defeats the point (they land in history).
#
# ==============================================================================


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Database (SECRET — contains credentials)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Single line, fully quoted. SRV URIs need a host with 3+ dot-separated labels.
MONGODB_URI="mongodb+srv://USER:PASSWORD@cluster.xxxxx.mongodb.net/DeCloud"


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Orchestrator wallet (SECRET — controls escrow funds)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The private key signs settlement transactions. Treat as production-critical
# even on testnet: anything that touches it should be rotated if exposed.
ORCHESTRATOR_WALLET_ADDRESS="0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000"
ORCHESTRATOR_PRIVATE_KEY="0xREPLACE_ME"


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth (SECRET)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Signing key for user JWTs. Rotating it invalidates all existing sessions.
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 48
JWT_SECRET_KEY="REPLACE_ME"


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare (SECRET — DNS-01 ACME challenges + subdomain records)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CLOUDFLARE_TOKEN="REPLACE_ME"
CLOUDFLARE_ZONE_ID="REPLACE_ME"


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Blockchain (NOT secret — safe as CLI flags too; here for convenience)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 80002 = Polygon Amoy testnet, 137 = Polygon mainnet.
BLOCKCHAIN_CHAIN_ID="80002"
BLOCKCHAIN_RPC_URL="https://polygon-amoy.drpc.org"
ESCROW_CONTRACT_ADDRESS="0xREPLACE_ME"
USDC_TOKEN_ADDRESS="0xREPLACE_ME"
REQUIRED_CONFIRMATIONS="20"


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Economics (NOT secret)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PLATFORM_FEE_PERCENT="10"
# MIN_SETTLEMENT_AMOUNT="1.0"


# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Networking (NOT secret)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ORCHESTRATOR_DOMAIN and CADDY_EMAIL have no side effects and are fine here,
# but keeping domains next to --ingress-domain on the command line makes the
# install invocation self-documenting. Pick one convention and stick to it.
#
# ORCHESTRATOR_DOMAIN="decloud.stackfi.tech"
# CADDY_EMAIL="admin@example.com"
# API_PORT="5050"
# TUNNEL_IP="10.20.0.1"
#
# DO NOT SET — see RULE 2:
#   INGRESS_DOMAIN / INSTALL_CADDY / ENABLE_INGRESS / ENABLE_WIREGUARD
